    {
      "id": "1314201896352874577",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2024-12-05T16:09:08.781+04:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "In general I don't think people should rely  on archive nodes for critical data, since there is little incentive for people to maintain and operate them, which means that there will only be a few entities running them, which goes against decentralization. Teams should be really careful about their strategies for securing data availability for their zkApps,  but I was wondering about if you can launch an archive node only for one or more specific zkApps.",
