      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "FYI, o1Labs is working on a better solution to this problem in general: https://www.o1labs.org/blog/introducing-project-untitled\n\nBut in the current world, nothing is stopping you!  The reason no one does (as far as I know) is that we haven't released a package that let's you decide what to keep and what to throw out.  Our archive node release (see: [getting started](https://docs.minaprotocol.com/node-operators/archive-node/getting-started)) stores everything by default, so you'd have to fork it and make some edits to save only data for a specific ZkApp or something.  Personally, I think that would be a great project for someone infrastructure-minded.",
