    {
      "id": "1314328672768888923",
      "type": "Reply",
      "timestamp": "2024-12-06T00:32:54.634+04:00",
      "timestampEdited": "2024-12-06T02:44:13.08+04:00",
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Haha, it kind of makes sense, since most people running archive nodes will mostly be running them as a service for everyone (like block explorers) rather than for a specific project. And that's fine, since one of the strongest points of Mina is being able to not care about historic state to run a full node, so it wouldn't make a lot of sense trying to incentivize archive nodes\n\nSomething like Project Untitled  that let you store the exact offchain state you want and update it (instead of storing every transaction and being limited to small data) makes more sense",
      "author": {
